colmenares called on comelec to not only issue clarifications but to actively prosecute those responsible under the omnibus election code we appreciate comelecs prompt statement confirming that bayan muna remains on the ballot however comelec must also use its full legal powers to investigate identify and prosecute those behind this criminal disinformation campaign he said kung hindi ito gagawin ng comelec ito ay magiging precedent na sa bawat eleksyon ay maaaring gamitin ang ganitong uri ng panlilinlang fake news of disqualification of candidates proliferated during the 2022 presidential elections we should put a stop to this otherwise it will be repeated in the 2028 presidential elections the former lawmaker also questioned the apparent involvement of state forces in the campaign the scale and coordination of these attacks from fake government documents to mock coffins appearing simultaneously across the country strongly suggest the involvement of state resources colmenares pointed out this is not only a violation of comelec rules but also of our antigraft laws for the misuse of public funds for partisan election campaigns despite these challenges colmenares expressed confidence in the discernment of filipino voters sa kabila ng lahat ng ito naniniwala kami sa katalinuhan at discernment ng mga pilipino they will see through these desperate tactics and vote according to their conscience and best interests he stated we call on our supporters to remain vigilant to report any instances of disinformation or intimidation and to exercise their right to vote with courage and conviction on may 12 colmenares concluded with a message of defiance sa mga nasa likod ng mga kasinungalingang ito hindi ninyo kami matatakot hindi ninyo mapipigilan ang boses ng mamamayan tuloy ang laban para sa tunay na demokrasya at para sa kapakanan ng mga marginalized at oppressed sectors ng ating lipunan

the supremecourtph in gr no 277540 balintay v comelec has granted the petition of chito bulatao balintay a member of the indigenous peoples of zambales reversing the comelec resolution that rejected his certificate of candidacy coc for zambales governor in the 2025 elections balintay filed his coc on the last day of filing 25 minutes prior to the closing time but since his coc was incomplete missing a required fifth copy and documentary stamps he was advised to complete his documents he returned 3 minutes past the 500 pm deadline the comelec rejected his coc citing section 37 of comelec resolution no 11045 the sc ruled that the comelec gravely abused its discretion when it did not allow balintay to file his coc it held that the comelec should reexamine whether its rules serve the interest of justice and fair play the sc ordered the comelec to accept balintays coc and include his name in the official ballots for zambales governor in the 2025 elections the sc on january 14 2025 had issued a temporary restraining order tro preventing the comelec from enforcing its decision rejecting balintays application read the full text of the press briefer at copying of this content is subject to the sc pios credit attribution policy

comelec vs respicio defending democracy or silencing critics so comelec just filed a cyber libel case against isabela vice mayoral candidate atty jeryll harold respicio for claiming that votecounting machines vcms can be manipulated and that backroom programs can alter election results on one hand comelec wants to protect the credibility of elections and thats a fight worth taking on the other are they trying to stop misinformation or shutting down a critic by the way hes a critic and not a hater haters dont criticize they hate 247 lets break it down why comelect has a point election disinformation is dangerous fake claims can erode public trust if people think elections are rigged before a single vote is cast why should we even bother voting comelec has to defend itself if they just let baseless accusations slide they allow the idea that the electoral process is a scam legal action has its place if respicio lied then yes he should be held accountable spreading false information especially about elections is reckless but lets not pretend this is a simple openandshut case why comelecs action is concerning shutting down critics isnt the same as proving them wrong why is comelecs first move a lawsuit instead of a public clarification instead of threatening legal action why not invite independent audits demonstrate safeguards and let facts speak for themselves this is a dangerous precedent disinformation is a problem but so is the government punishing critics especially when the case involves disqualification disbarment and revoking his cpa license is this about election integrity or sending a message to anyone who dares to challenge the system what if theres even a sliver of truth if atty respicio has zero evidence he deserves to be called out but what if theres something worth looking into filing cases instead of addressing concerns only fuels more doubt heres the problem atty respicio made bold claims without evidence if youre going to say the system is rigged you better come with solid proof otherwise youre just adding to the noise comelecs response to me feels like overkill a libel case a disqualification case a disbarment case a license revocation thats not just holding someone accountable thats obliterating them this could have been handled better comelec should have challenged atty respicio to provide proof if none exists debunk it with facts atty respicio should have backed up his claims or explicitly claimed he was just speculating both sides should have engaged in a discussion instead of launching into legal warfare unlike fake news peddlers atty respicio was trying to point out an issue with the vcm machines worth looking into comelec should have proven atty respicio wrong by presenting facts and accountability suing a vice mayoral candidate doesnt restore trust in elections but debunking his claims that just might

comelec no grounds to halt proclamation of leila de lima despite ca ruling the commission on elections comelec sees no reason to suspend the proclamation of mamamayang liberal ml partylist first nominee leila de lima despite the court of appeals ca recent ruling involving one of her previously dismissed drug cases comelec chair george garcia said on friday may 16 that the ca ruling does not amount to a final conviction and therefore has no bearing on the partylists proclamation wala po tayong nakikitang kadahilanan upang ipahinto ang proklamasyon sapagkat hindi naman po final conviction yon at ang alam po natin bilang isang abogado ang decision ng court of appeals ay subject sa motion for reconsideration kung hindi man pepwede maitaas din sa supreme court garcia said at a press conference the ca earlier nullified a 2023 decision by the muntinlupa regional trial court rtc branch 204 that acquitted de lima and remanded the case for clarification citing a lack of clarity in the trial courts explanation of its ruling in a chance interview department of justice doj spokesperson mico clavano clarified that the cas action was not a direct reversal of de limas acquittal this is not a reversal per se it is more of a remanding of the decisionto clarify he said adding that the office of the solicitor general osg will handle the case and that de lima may still file a motion for reconsideration de lima now congresswomanelect under the ml partylist vowed to appeal the decision and proceed with her return to public service hindi ito magiging hadlang sa pagbabalik ko sa serbisyopubliko at ipagpapatuloy ko ang aking preparasyon sa pagsulong ng hustisya at reporma sa kongreso she said in a statement

2025 philippine senate elections a political earthquake with most of the votes transmitted to the comelec servers in manila the 2025 senate race has delivered some unexpected outcomes dutertealigned candidates dominate the dutertebacked coalition duterten secured 5 seats in the senate notably senator bong go led the race with over 24 million votes followed by ronald bato dela rosa and rodante marcoleta who outperformed preelection surveys this strong showing underscores the enduring influence of the duterte brand particularly in mindanao and the visayas regions this will be including imee and villar marcos administrations alyansa underperforms in contrast the marcosbacked alyansa para sa bagong pilipinas secured only 5 seats falling short of expectations set by preelection polls highprofile candidates like imee marcos and camille villar did not make it to the top 12 highlighting a significant shift in voter sentiment opposition makes surprising gains the opposition particularly the kibam coalition made unexpected gains bam aquino and kiko pangilinan previously trailing in polls secured seats in the senate indicating a resurgence of antiadministration sentiment in key regions polling firms face scrutiny the election results have cast doubt on the reliability of major polling firms like pulse asia and sws their preelection surveys failed to capture the late shifts in voter preferences leading to significant discrepancies between predicted and actual outcomes side take aways prep for the battle of whos the stronger candidate endorser as despite being embattled vp sara pushed more candidates to her side than the safer silent pink notable were the last 2 candidates pushed by them villar and imee vs pacquiao and abalos much to be said here there is also much to be said about the inc push thats not needed for some but might have neutered some candidates to being overtly antagonistic over impeachment personal take the diffusion of gold standard polling is now broken with old models not working unless there is a clear winner i think the pollsters with their leanings over corrected their bias against the admin all admin understating data of a particular anti admin undertone this time their instinctual bias was correct imo marcoleta dark horse now presumed senator marcoleta is the trillanes of the now a message strongly to the powers of a sentiment to any administration not to rest on his laurels and for the liberals a fearful taste that one who buried abscbn go his just rewards another one is sen bong go who is now probably in the 25m more on that later power structures are being reformed what it means to be a filipino is being defined and what we end up seeing in its core despite the distractions is who gets to decide what we do in our country and our own exciting times ahead and we will see if the message of the people is heard loud and clear
